<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,261,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Plate extremely long, with apex right-angled dorsally, apex of plate reaching anal tube, apex narrow tubular (
<figureCitation box="[363,469,298,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2 a</figureCitation>
). Pygofer rectangular, pygofer lobe reduced (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1146,298,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="54.[151,258,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,201,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-85@54.[180,1407,197,1753]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 1 a–l. Pravistylus species. Pygofer, laterally. a, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; b, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; c, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; d, P. caenophallus sp. n.; e, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; f–g, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; h, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; i–k, P.eductus(Naudé); l, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
aj). Female sternite 7 longitudinally rectangular, with short triangular ligula (
<figureCitation box="[797,867,336,362]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="70.[151,255,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[228,1356,197,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-105@70.[225,1359,194,1900]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 7 a–af. Pravistylus species. Sternite 7 of female, whole structure, or posterior margin. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; c, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; d, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; e–f, P. caenophallus sp. n.; g–i, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; j–l, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; m–n, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; o–t, P. eductus (Naudé); u–w, P. exquadratus (Naudé); x–aa, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n.; ab–af, P. interdiscus sp. n." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
cf).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,331,373,399]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology</emphasis>
. Latin, 
<emphasis box="[426,522,373,398]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">varicus,</emphasis>
straddling, 
<emphasis box="[666,750,373,398]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">discus¸</emphasis>
disc, i.e. subgenital plate; for the nature of the plate that straddles the pygofer and with its apex reaching the anal tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,415,447,473]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Male and female</emphasis>
. Ochraceous, male with variable narrow fuscous marking on dorsally on pygofer. Female ochraceous, unmarked. Both sexes sometimes with more distinct fuscous marking on vertex and inner anteapical cell of tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[468,543,522,548]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="73.[151,255,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,194,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-70@73.[213,1373,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 8 a–h. Pravistylus species. Habitus. a–b, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., a, male; b, female; c–d, P. brachyplacus sp. n., c, male; d, female; e, P. caenophallus sp. n., male; f–g, P. deltoplacus sp. n., male; h, P. dentidiscus sp. n., male." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 8</figureCitation>
bm &amp; bn).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,260,559,585]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,421,559,585]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Dimensions</emphasis>
. (n = 25) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[542,632,559,585]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Length</emphasis>
: to tegmina 
<quantity box="[784,930,560,586]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="2.3499999999999996" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.4 mm</quantity>
; to abdomen 
<quantity box="[1091,1238,560,586]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.9 mm</quantity>
; vertex medially 
<quantity box="[151,295,597,623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 mm</quantity>
; vertex next to eye 
<quantity box="[521,613,597,623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; pronotum medially 
<quantity box="[855,948,597,623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[958,1037,597,623]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Width</emphasis>
: head 
<quantity box="[1114,1207,597,623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
; pronotum 
<quantity box="[1339,1432,597,623]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
. Ocellar diameter 28.0 µm; ocellocular distance 37.0–45.9 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,392,671,697]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Genital capsule</emphasis>
. Pygofer rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[661,732,672,698]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="54.[151,258,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,201,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-85@54.[180,1407,197,1753]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 1 a–l. Pravistylus species. Pygofer, laterally. a, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; b, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; c, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; d, P. caenophallus sp. n.; e, P. deltoplacus sp. n.; f–g, P. dentidiscus sp. n.; h, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; i–k, P.eductus(Naudé); l, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
aj). Pygofer lobe reduced, subapical, broadly merged with pygofer. Plate elongate, more so than in any other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theron" authorityYear="1975" box="[877,1009,709,734]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[877,1009,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pravistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; basal two thirds acutely triangular, basal lateral margin slightly sinuous, sparsely set with fine, short setae; plate 2.4–2.7 times as long as width across base (excluding length of right-angled apex); apex narrow, tubular, sclerotized, right-angled dorsally, apex in repose reaching as far as anal tube; 6–7 uniseriate marginal medial macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1294,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1711,1735]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,205,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-63@57.[190,1396,194,1718]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 2 a–i. Pravistylus species. Plate, part or whole structure. a, P. varicudiscus sp. n.; b, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; c, P. digitidiscus sp. n.; d, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; e–g, P.eductus(Naudé); h–i, P. exquadratus (Naudé)." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 2 a</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme narrow; shaft, ventral view, narrow, parallel-sided; lateral view, wide at base, basal ⅔ uniformly curved dorsad, apical ⅓ deflected somewhat ventrad; gonopore subapical, dorsolaterad (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1393,896,922]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="62.[151,255,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[249,1353,187,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-126@62.[233,1361,182,1903]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 3 a–t. Pravistylus species. Aedeagus, laterally. a–b, P.lobus sp. n.; c, P. deltoplacussp. n.; d, P. mecophysis sp. n.; e, P. bidentidiscus sp. n.; f, P. brachyplacus sp. n.; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n.; h, P. mecistoplacus sp. n.; i–k, P. mutilidiscus sp. n.; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n.; m, P. odontiophallus sp. n.; n–o, P.eductus (Naudé); p–q, P. exquadratus (Naudé); r, P. tanyoplacus sp. n.; s, P. macropygeus sp. n.; t, P. pollediscus sp. n." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Figs 3</figureCitation>
ag, 4 ae). Style distal part widely separated from basal medial arm; apophysis acutely triangular, about 6 teeth ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[273,345,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="66.[151,255,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[198,1391,200,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-128@66.[190,1397,194,1814]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 5 a–p. Pravistylus species. Style, dorsally or ventrally. a–b, P. eductus (Naudé), ventral; c–d, P. exquadratus (Naudé), ventral; e, P. longitrunculus sp. n., ventral; f, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., ventral; g, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; j, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; l, P. brachyphysis sp. n., dorsal; m, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; n, P. deltoplacus sp. n., ventral; o–p, P. dentidiscus sp. n., ventral." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
al). Connective elongate, stem triangular, about twice as wide as width across arms (
<figureCitation box="[1365,1436,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="69.[151,256,1720,1744]" captionTargetBox="[266,1320,198,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-273@69.[264,1329,194,1706]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURE 6 a–ai. Pravistylus species. Connective, dorsally or ventrally and laterally. a, P. lobus sp. n., ventral; b, P. deltoplacus sp. n., dorsal; c, P. mecophysis sp. n., dorsal; d, P. bidentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; e, P. brachyplacus sp. n., dorsal; f, P. mollidiscus sp. n., dorsal; g, P. mecistoplacus sp. n., dorsal; h, P. mutilidiscus sp. n., dorsal; i, P. brachyphysis sp. n., ventral; j, P. odontiophallus sp. n., dorsal; k, P. odontiophallus sp. n., ventral; l, P.eductus(Naudé), dorsal; m, P. eductus (Naudé), lateral; n–o, P. exquadratus (Naudé), dorsal; p, P. exquadratus (Naudé), lateral; q, P. tanyoplacus sp. n., dorsal; r, P. macropygeus sp. n., dorsal; s–u, P. pollediscus sp. n., dorsal; v, P. scolopygeus sp. n., dorsal; w, P. dentidiscus sp. n., dorsal; x, P. micropygeus sp. n., dorsal; y, P. trunculidiscus sp. n., dorsal; z, P. longitrunculus sp. n., dorsal; aa, P. digitidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ab, P. serratus sp. n., dorsal; ac, P. indistinctidiscus sp. n., dorsal; ad, P. odontopygeus sp. n., dorsal; ae, P. varicudiscus sp. n., ventral; af, P. pelorophallus sp. n., ventral; ag, P. pelorophallus sp. n., lateral; ah, P. scolophallus sp. n., ventral; ai, P. caenophallus sp. n., ventral." pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
ae).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,261,1706]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,287,1045,1071]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Female</emphasis>
